1
00:00:05,171 --> 00:00:07,039
<i>Building our own office tower,</i>

2
00:00:07,040 --> 00:00:11,044
<i>acquiring a bank, developing AI…</i>

3
00:00:11,778 --> 00:00:14,014
<i>I, Kosei Neo, was living</i>

4
00:00:14,581 --> 00:00:17,217
<i>as the president of NEOXIS…</i>

5
00:00:18,985 --> 00:00:22,121
<i>when someone shoved me from behind.</i>

6
00:00:22,122 --> 00:00:24,557
<i>I should have died.</i>

7
00:00:26,159 --> 00:00:28,060
<i>But by some miracle, I came back</i>

8
00:00:28,061 --> 00:00:30,463
<i>from cardiac arrest.</i>

9
00:00:31,364 --> 00:00:35,568
<i>The body looked just like my own,</i>

10
00:00:36,269 --> 00:00:37,903
<i>but something was off.</i>

11
00:00:37,904 --> 00:00:42,175
"Shinzo Abe returns
to the position of prime minister."

12
00:00:42,776 --> 00:00:44,677
"2012."

13
00:00:45,245 --> 00:00:47,112
"End of the year weather report"?

14
00:00:47,113 --> 00:00:51,216
<i>Eiji Nomoto, the man I'd dragged
into that fall,</i>

15
00:00:51,217 --> 00:00:53,286
<i>treated me like his son</i>

16
00:00:53,920 --> 00:00:58,091
<i>and brought me back to the shopping street
I'd forced out of business.</i>

17
00:00:59,159 --> 00:01:02,828
<i>You lost consciousness protecting Sarasa.</i>

18
00:01:02,829 --> 00:01:04,663
Thanks for saving me.

19
00:01:04,664 --> 00:01:09,536
<i>And I look exactly like Eito Nomoto,
who should be dead.</i>

20
00:01:10,603 --> 00:01:14,274
<i>I was reborn into his body
and came back to life.</i>

21
00:01:15,375 --> 00:01:16,309
But why?

22
00:01:17,577 --> 00:01:21,815
THE DAY AFTER BEING REBORN

23
00:01:39,365 --> 00:01:42,768
DECEMBER 2012

24
00:01:42,769 --> 00:01:44,270
<i>Am I really going to live</i>

25
00:01:45,238 --> 00:01:48,108
<i>in this house now?</i>

26
00:01:58,451 --> 00:02:02,455
<i>That's Eito's mother.</i>

27
00:02:04,491 --> 00:02:09,395
<i>As a devoted son,
should I be offering incense?</i>

28
00:02:10,997 --> 00:02:14,200
<i>Maybe Eito did this every morning.</i>

29
00:02:18,571 --> 00:02:20,707
- That's unusual.
- Unusual indeed.

30
00:02:21,407 --> 00:02:24,277
Well, Mom must be happy.

31
00:02:27,580 --> 00:02:29,282
All right, let's have breakfast.

32
00:02:43,296 --> 00:02:46,366
<i>Tsukudani… and ohitashi.</i>

33
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:49,135
- <i>These are my least favorite foods.</i>
- What's wrong?

34
00:02:50,036 --> 00:02:52,172
I made all of your favorites.

35
00:02:56,576 --> 00:03:00,013
<i>Of all things, he picked
my absolute least favorite, bettarazuke.</i>

36
00:03:01,481 --> 00:03:03,683
<i>But wait…</i>

37
00:03:04,250 --> 00:03:08,388
<i>This is Eito's body now,
so maybe it actually tastes good to him.</i>

38
00:03:11,691 --> 00:03:13,292
<i>Nope. Still can't do it.</i>

39
00:03:13,293 --> 00:03:16,629
NOMOTO DRY CLEANERS

40
00:03:21,868 --> 00:03:23,603
Eito, switch back with me.

41
00:03:32,579 --> 00:03:34,080
What are you doing?

42
00:03:34,647 --> 00:03:36,349
You use this for that ketchup stain.

43
00:03:42,689 --> 00:03:45,325
Hey! Wait a second!

44
00:03:47,794 --> 00:03:48,628
What's wrong, Eito?

45
00:03:50,463 --> 00:03:51,931
I'm so sorry!

46
00:03:53,466 --> 00:03:57,804
I must've hit my head pretty hard.
I keep spacing out.

47
00:04:01,541 --> 00:04:05,510
- Eito, can you take care of this? Thanks.
- Thanks.

48
00:04:05,511 --> 00:04:06,512
Um…

49
00:04:08,214 --> 00:04:10,550
What about a receipt or a fee?

50
00:04:13,786 --> 00:04:15,088
What are you talking about?

51
00:04:15,822 --> 00:04:17,824
I always put it on my tab.

52
00:04:19,158 --> 00:04:20,260
<i>On tab?</i>

53
00:04:21,394 --> 00:04:24,364
<i>That's the worst way to run a business.</i>

54
00:04:24,998 --> 00:04:25,832
You okay?

55
00:04:26,399 --> 00:04:27,634
Oh, yeah.

56
00:04:29,002 --> 00:04:30,036
Of course, right?

57
00:04:30,603 --> 00:04:32,238
"Right?"

58
00:04:33,239 --> 00:04:36,742
You okay?
That's not how you usually speak.

59
00:04:36,743 --> 00:04:37,577
Go rest.

60
00:04:39,379 --> 00:04:42,415
- Hey!
- <i>What am I supposed to do here?</i>

61
00:04:42,982 --> 00:04:44,716
Everyone's come to visit.

62
00:04:44,717 --> 00:04:46,051
Don't run!

63
00:04:46,052 --> 00:04:47,886
Sorry for this…

64
00:04:47,887 --> 00:04:50,422
Yeah, everyone came…

65
00:04:50,423 --> 00:04:51,523
Mom must be happy.

66
00:04:51,524 --> 00:04:52,524
That's great!

67
00:04:52,525 --> 00:04:53,792
Come on, put some light on.

68
00:04:53,793 --> 00:04:55,794
- Here's some juice!
- Here!

69
00:04:55,795 --> 00:04:57,796
Come here!

70
00:04:57,797 --> 00:04:59,564
Here! Oh, no!

71
00:04:59,565 --> 00:05:01,466
- No!
- Sorry about that!

72
00:05:01,467 --> 00:05:04,103
- No, it's better to have energetic kids…
- Mom…

73
00:05:05,405 --> 00:05:06,439
You know the other day…

74
00:05:07,540 --> 00:05:08,540
<i>So annoying!</i>

75
00:05:08,541 --> 00:05:10,242
You okay?

76
00:05:10,243 --> 00:05:11,143
<i>I want to be alone.</i>

77
00:05:11,144 --> 00:05:13,412
All right, the rice is ready.

78
00:05:13,413 --> 00:05:15,347
The rice is done.

79
00:05:15,348 --> 00:05:17,049
Here, rice balls.

80
00:05:17,050 --> 00:05:18,183
Go ahead and eat.

81
00:05:18,184 --> 00:05:19,251
Rice balls?

82
00:05:19,252 --> 00:05:20,752
I'm going to make more.

83
00:05:20,753 --> 00:05:23,189
- First,
- Alright!

84
00:05:23,756 --> 00:05:25,224
as a get-well celebration…

85
00:05:25,892 --> 00:05:27,360
- <i>Bare hands?</i>
- Eito first…

86
00:05:29,696 --> 00:05:31,863
Oh, no!

87
00:05:31,864 --> 00:05:33,433
<i>Unsanitary…</i>

88
00:05:34,033 --> 00:05:34,966
Sorry to keep you waiting.

89
00:05:34,967 --> 00:05:36,134
Yeah!

90
00:05:36,135 --> 00:05:38,303
<i>It's the woman</i>

91
00:05:38,304 --> 00:05:41,373
- <i>Eito risked his life to protect.</i>
- From Dad to Eito…

92
00:05:41,374 --> 00:05:42,708
DASSAI RICE WINE

93
00:05:42,709 --> 00:05:46,579
<i>Come to think of it,
there was a Dassai craze back then.</i>

94
00:05:47,246 --> 00:05:49,881
<i>The highest token of gratitude</i>

95
00:05:49,882 --> 00:05:54,219
<i>from a father to the man
who saved his daughter.</i>

96
00:05:54,220 --> 00:05:55,921
Eito, you're here?

97
00:05:55,922 --> 00:05:57,657
You're here!

98
00:05:58,558 --> 00:06:01,727
- Chairman, what happened?
- You know…

99
00:06:01,728 --> 00:06:03,595
You're young!

100
00:06:03,596 --> 00:06:06,099
Oh, that's right!

101
00:06:06,733 --> 00:06:09,401
Hey, Eito! Look!

102
00:06:09,402 --> 00:06:11,470
It's your beloved Dassai!

103
00:06:11,471 --> 00:06:14,439
- Dad, don't make him drink so much!
- Yeah!

104
00:06:14,440 --> 00:06:16,108
It's only been a short time

105
00:06:16,109 --> 00:06:17,008
- since the accident…
- <i>No way…</i>

106
00:06:17,009 --> 00:06:18,911
It's Dassai!

107
00:06:20,213 --> 00:06:23,081
<i>Back when I was Kosei Neo,</i>

108
00:06:23,082 --> 00:06:27,120
<i>this man had his livelihood
taken away due to my company's pressure.</i>

109
00:06:28,054 --> 00:06:30,189
<i>He's Sarasa's father.</i>

110
00:06:31,057 --> 00:06:32,492
<i>And later on…</i>

111
00:06:35,161 --> 00:06:36,628
Dassai! Here you go!

112
00:06:36,629 --> 00:06:38,363
I know.

113
00:06:38,364 --> 00:06:39,398
It's fine.

114
00:06:39,399 --> 00:06:40,299
I'm sorry.

115
00:06:41,534 --> 00:06:44,836
I'll go back to my room.

116
00:06:44,837 --> 00:06:46,705
- Oh, come on.
- What?

117
00:06:46,706 --> 00:06:47,973
Eito, what's wrong?

118
00:06:47,974 --> 00:06:49,474
You say too much!

119
00:06:49,475 --> 00:06:50,810
Was it me?

120
00:07:00,486 --> 00:07:02,922
We killed that man!

121
00:07:03,489 --> 00:07:06,191
<i>Kinpei Iketani, Sarasa's father,</i>

122
00:07:06,192 --> 00:07:09,729
<i>took his own life due to financial ruin.</i>

123
00:07:10,663 --> 00:07:14,332
<i>If he had never been in financial trouble,</i>

124
00:07:14,333 --> 00:07:16,736
<i>could that death have been prevented?</i>

125
00:07:20,006 --> 00:07:21,541
<i>Kosei Neo is really acting like</i>

126
00:07:22,508 --> 00:07:24,677
<i>a good guy all of a sudden.</i>

127
00:07:27,146 --> 00:07:29,681
<i>I pushed forward,</i>

128
00:07:29,682 --> 00:07:32,551
<i>believing that</i>

129
00:07:32,552 --> 00:07:34,587
<i>some sacrifices were worth a greater good.</i>

130
00:07:36,522 --> 00:07:38,191
<i>How do I come back from that?</i>

131
00:07:39,659 --> 00:07:43,261
<i>Wait. I exist in this era</i>

132
00:07:43,262 --> 00:07:46,666
<i>with Kosei Neo's soul.</i>

133
00:07:47,166 --> 00:07:49,769
<i>So what's happening
to the real Kosei Neo right now?</i>

134
00:07:50,770 --> 00:07:52,904
<i>In sci-fi novels,</i>

135
00:07:52,905 --> 00:07:54,172
<i>a time traveler</i>

136
00:07:54,173 --> 00:07:57,576
<i>isn't allowed to alter someone's fate</i>

137
00:07:57,577 --> 00:08:03,015
<i>or have two versions of the same person
exist at once.</i>

138
00:08:04,650 --> 00:08:09,454
<i>If those rules apply here, then maybe
the original Kosei Neo's body and all</i>

139
00:08:09,455 --> 00:08:13,092
<i>have vanished from this world.</i>

140
00:08:15,428 --> 00:08:19,598
<i>Which means the NEOXIS staff</i>

141
00:08:19,599 --> 00:08:22,334
<i>might be waiting anxiously
for Kosei Neo to return.</i>

142
00:08:22,335 --> 00:08:23,803
SANYOKAN BUILDING

143
00:08:25,972 --> 00:08:27,173
<i>Found it.</i>

144
00:08:28,074 --> 00:08:29,742
<i>NEOXIS's rental office,</i>

145
00:08:30,409 --> 00:08:32,912
<i>the one we used
before building our own tower.</i>

146
00:08:34,380 --> 00:08:35,381
<i>Okay.</i>

147
00:08:38,150 --> 00:08:40,720
Please wait for check-in.

148
00:08:41,420 --> 00:08:43,990
I'm Kosei Neo of NEOXIS.

149
00:08:46,359 --> 00:08:49,295
Please show your visitor pass
or employee ID.

150
00:08:50,663 --> 00:08:52,932
You don't recognize my face?

151
00:08:56,135 --> 00:08:57,737
- One moment.
- Yes.

152
00:08:58,938 --> 00:09:00,573
One moment.

153
00:09:01,807 --> 00:09:03,309
He's already clocked in.

154
00:09:05,144 --> 00:09:09,948
President Neo has already arrived
and is currently in the building.

155
00:09:09,949 --> 00:09:13,019
Two versions of the same person
exist at the same time?

156
00:09:14,120 --> 00:09:15,321
Excuse me?

157
00:09:16,022 --> 00:09:20,860
<i>Calm down. I've always found a way
through every obstacle like this.</i>

158
00:09:21,961 --> 00:09:24,496
<i>Maybe if I explain the situation,</i>

159
00:09:24,497 --> 00:09:27,567
<i>the Kosei Neo of this era
would understand.</i>

160
00:09:29,435 --> 00:09:30,702
<i>Right.</i>

161
00:09:30,703 --> 00:09:32,537
<i>If there are two of us,</i>

162
00:09:32,538 --> 00:09:37,043
<i>the company might grow twice as fast,
and he might even welcome me.</i>

163
00:09:39,412 --> 00:09:42,881
Anyway, please let me see Kosei Neo.

164
00:09:42,882 --> 00:09:44,349
- Hold on.
- No!

165
00:09:44,350 --> 00:09:45,317
- First…
- No!

166
00:09:45,318 --> 00:09:46,851
Please come with us to security.

167
00:09:46,852 --> 00:09:49,120
Oh. Understood.

168
00:09:49,121 --> 00:09:51,122
Hey wait!

169
00:09:51,123 --> 00:09:52,191
Wait!

170
00:09:56,128 --> 00:09:59,732
- That wasn't the president now, right?
- He was a suspicious person.

171
00:10:05,037 --> 00:10:09,375
<i>This is beyond anything I imagined.</i>

172
00:10:11,911 --> 00:10:15,715
<i>If the original Kosei Neo
actually exists here,</i>

173
00:10:16,282 --> 00:10:19,918
<i>who am I supposed to live as?</i>

174
00:10:19,919 --> 00:10:23,288
Eito!

175
00:10:23,289 --> 00:10:25,323
- Where were you?
- Hey!

176
00:10:25,324 --> 00:10:27,325
- Eito! Your dad…
- <i>So…</i>

177
00:10:27,326 --> 00:10:29,295
<i>Kosei Neo's soul…</i>

178
00:10:29,929 --> 00:10:31,563
<i>has no choice</i>

179
00:10:31,564 --> 00:10:35,434
<i>but to live in Eito Nomoto's body?</i>

180
00:10:46,612 --> 00:10:47,947
<i>But even so,</i>

181
00:10:49,015 --> 00:10:51,150
<i>living as Eito</i>

182
00:10:51,784 --> 00:10:53,518
<i>is going to be incredibly hard.</i>

183
00:10:53,519 --> 00:10:56,655
NOMOTO DRY CLEANERS

184
00:10:56,656 --> 00:10:57,657
On top of that,

185
00:10:58,624 --> 00:11:00,359
there are not many customers.

186
00:11:09,502 --> 00:11:12,571
Is the business doing okay?

187
00:11:19,745 --> 00:11:21,414
BANK BOOK

188
00:11:26,285 --> 00:11:28,454
This is bad.

189
00:11:29,055 --> 00:11:31,556
The shopping street people

190
00:11:31,557 --> 00:11:33,926
aren't paying their tabs,

191
00:11:34,794 --> 00:11:36,995
and we're in the red every month.

192
00:11:36,996 --> 00:11:38,296
LOAN NOTE

193
00:11:38,297 --> 00:11:42,635
And the debt is exactly 10 million yen.

194
00:11:50,176 --> 00:11:53,779
This is going to affect me too,
living as Eito.

195
00:11:54,914 --> 00:11:56,048
<i>With this situation,</i>

196
00:11:56,682 --> 00:11:59,017
<i>I can't even buy the wine I want.</i>

197
00:11:59,018 --> 00:12:01,486
Don't drink that! Hey!

198
00:12:01,487 --> 00:12:03,956
- Come on!
- Hey!

199
00:12:04,724 --> 00:12:08,394
If only the shopping street could thrive
and bring in some money…

200
00:12:09,128 --> 00:12:10,562
That would at least help a little.

201
00:12:10,563 --> 00:12:12,198
‎-That guy…
‎-No way!

202
00:12:14,233 --> 00:12:15,367
But…

203
00:12:16,469 --> 00:12:17,837
drinking from the morning…

204
00:12:20,406 --> 00:12:21,640
Are they just idiots?

205
00:12:23,509 --> 00:12:25,477
- He's coming…
- You sure?

206
00:12:25,478 --> 00:12:28,146
‎-No way!
‎-When was that?

207
00:12:28,147 --> 00:12:29,481
‎Come on!

208
00:12:29,482 --> 00:12:32,151
No customers are coming anyway.
Eito, come over here.

209
00:12:33,085 --> 00:12:35,553
Hold on, Eiji-san.

210
00:12:35,554 --> 00:12:38,858
You can't just do nothing
when we're struggling like this.

211
00:12:40,092 --> 00:12:42,628
Eiji-san? Are you okay?

212
00:12:43,195 --> 00:12:45,163
I'm speaking perfectly reasonably.

213
00:12:45,164 --> 00:12:47,767
You don't sound like Eito at all.

214
00:12:48,834 --> 00:12:50,102
Want to go back to the hospital?

215
00:12:51,670 --> 00:12:52,505
No.

216
00:12:53,539 --> 00:12:56,674
Yeah!

217
00:12:56,675 --> 00:13:01,647
<i>First, I need to build a foundation
to keep life running.</i>

218
00:13:03,582 --> 00:13:07,552
<i>For that, I need information</i>

219
00:13:07,553 --> 00:13:09,522
<i>about how to live as Eito.</i>

220
00:13:11,457 --> 00:13:12,657
<i>Thank you.</i>

221
00:13:12,658 --> 00:13:15,727
CHICKEN SKEWERS

222
00:13:15,728 --> 00:13:17,329
<i>Delicious. So good!</i>

223
00:13:18,497 --> 00:13:20,031
- <i>Wow!</i>
- <i>Good?</i>

224
00:13:20,032 --> 00:13:21,199
<i>I'm glad!</i>

225
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:24,135
- <i>Truly outstanding.</i>
- <i>Absolutely outstanding.</i>

226
00:13:24,136 --> 00:13:27,373
- <i>Seriously…</i>
- Absolutely outstanding.

227
00:13:29,542 --> 00:13:32,243
<i>I'm going for it! Once I decide,
I never back down.</i>

228
00:13:32,244 --> 00:13:33,845
<i>Really?</i>

229
00:13:33,846 --> 00:13:37,482
I'm going for it! Once I decide,
I never back down.

230
00:13:37,483 --> 00:13:40,519
- <i>I love Akari Shopping Street.</i>
- <i>Yeah.</i>

231
00:13:41,453 --> 00:13:44,390
<i>Giving up without trying
is absolute garbage!</i>

232
00:13:45,090 --> 00:13:48,561
Giving up without trying
is absolute garbage!

233
00:13:51,797 --> 00:13:53,599
Absolute garbage!

234
00:13:57,703 --> 00:14:00,004
What are you doing?

235
00:14:00,005 --> 00:14:02,240
Were you just doing an impression
of yourself?

236
00:14:02,241 --> 00:14:03,776
I knew it. What an idiot.

237
00:14:04,510 --> 00:14:08,780
<i>Being called an idiot
by a plain idiot is deeply disagreeable,</i>

238
00:14:08,781 --> 00:14:11,449
<i>but I'll let it slide for now.</i>

239
00:14:11,450 --> 00:14:12,384
Eito.

240
00:14:13,018 --> 00:14:14,954
- What's wrong, Sarasa?
- Did something happen?

241
00:14:15,621 --> 00:14:18,891
Apparently, a big supermarket is opening
in the building by the station.

242
00:14:19,558 --> 00:14:22,293
<i>Super Soman! Grand opening, February 5th.</i>

243
00:14:22,294 --> 00:14:26,331
Chairman, if a big supermarket opens up,

244
00:14:26,332 --> 00:14:28,167
what's going to happen
to our shopping street?

245
00:14:29,501 --> 00:14:32,003
We barely have any customers as it is.

246
00:14:32,004 --> 00:14:33,772
This could get rough.

247
00:14:34,974 --> 00:14:37,776
<i>So that's what's going on.</i>

248
00:14:38,944 --> 00:14:41,112
<i>Now, what ideas
will the shopping street crew</i>

249
00:14:41,113 --> 00:14:43,181
<i>come up with</i>

250
00:14:43,182 --> 00:14:45,184
<i>to face this crisis?</i>

251
00:14:47,319 --> 00:14:50,055
In times like these, the only thing to do…

252
00:14:51,757 --> 00:14:52,724
is drink.

253
00:14:52,725 --> 00:14:53,725
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

254
00:14:53,726 --> 00:14:55,594
- Yeah!
- Let's do it!

255
00:14:58,631 --> 00:14:59,931
I'm first!

256
00:14:59,932 --> 00:15:01,300
<i>Drink and forget about it?</i>

257
00:15:02,468 --> 00:15:04,936
<i>In a crisis like this? Reality…</i>

258
00:15:04,937 --> 00:15:06,671
- Hey!
- Oh!

259
00:15:06,672 --> 00:15:08,072
Everyone!

260
00:15:08,073 --> 00:15:10,808
Hideko fried some croquettes
and minced meat croquettes for everyone!

261
00:15:10,809 --> 00:15:12,710
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

262
00:15:12,711 --> 00:15:14,279
- Yeah!
- Okay!

263
00:15:14,280 --> 00:15:17,148
I just fried them, so dig in!

264
00:15:17,149 --> 00:15:18,917
Kinpei!

265
00:15:18,918 --> 00:15:20,985
- Here!
- Yeah!

266
00:15:20,986 --> 00:15:23,187
Eito, you too, eat up!

267
00:15:23,188 --> 00:15:24,856
‎-Why was that?
‎-No…

268
00:15:24,857 --> 00:15:26,724
- With rice wine…
- Yeah…

269
00:15:26,725 --> 00:15:29,894
‎-What?
‎-That's what we say…

270
00:15:29,895 --> 00:15:32,665
‎-We don't need that…
‎-No!

271
00:15:33,933 --> 00:15:35,566
‎-The tartar sauce is better.
‎-Yeah.

272
00:15:35,567 --> 00:15:38,002
‎-They're kids, so stop…
‎-Watch out!

273
00:15:38,003 --> 00:15:40,472
What is this? This is incredible.

274
00:15:47,279 --> 00:15:49,148
Unbelievably good…

275
00:15:51,984 --> 00:15:53,719
You scared me.

276
00:15:55,921 --> 00:15:56,821
This is good.

277
00:15:56,822 --> 00:15:58,156
- Sarasa…
- This is good.

278
00:15:58,157 --> 00:15:59,357
- For sure…
- Hey!

279
00:15:59,358 --> 00:16:00,692
- It fills you up.
- What?

280
00:16:00,693 --> 00:16:02,026
So yeah…

281
00:16:02,027 --> 00:16:04,029
- Want the minced meat croquette?
- Yeah.

282
00:16:04,663 --> 00:16:05,497
Here.

283
00:16:06,332 --> 00:16:09,000
‎-What the heck?
‎-What?

284
00:16:09,001 --> 00:16:10,668
This is good. For me…

285
00:16:10,669 --> 00:16:11,769
- Oh?
- Really…

286
00:16:11,770 --> 00:16:12,871
Absolutely

287
00:16:13,739 --> 00:16:14,873
outstanding!

288
00:16:15,874 --> 00:16:17,608
‎-Adds depth of flavor.
‎-What?

289
00:16:17,609 --> 00:16:19,077
‎-Huh?
‎-Tastes good.

290
00:16:19,078 --> 00:16:20,479
<i>I remembered.</i>

291
00:16:22,481 --> 00:16:26,250
<i>There was a shopping street
that thrived on its fried food.</i>

292
00:16:26,251 --> 00:16:28,720
‎-What are you saying? You…
‎-No!

293
00:16:28,721 --> 00:16:29,555
This is it!

294
00:16:30,255 --> 00:16:32,123
But you know…

295
00:16:32,124 --> 00:16:33,025
- This is it!
- Huh?

296
00:16:34,827 --> 00:16:37,295
We'll use this amazing fried food
to draw people in,

297
00:16:37,296 --> 00:16:40,132
revitalize the shopping street,
and take on the supermarket!

298
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:42,300
Take them on?

299
00:16:42,301 --> 00:16:43,836
Are you serious, Eito?

300
00:16:44,636 --> 00:16:47,271
An IT firm with its own pro baseball team

301
00:16:47,272 --> 00:16:50,542
is moving into the supermarket business.
We can't compete.

302
00:16:51,276 --> 00:16:52,910
Wait, are you saying…

303
00:16:52,911 --> 00:16:55,013
- <i>It has been said that an IT firm…</i>
- That supermarket…

304
00:16:55,014 --> 00:16:57,548
- <i>…having its own team was impossible…</i>
- It's the president of Super Soman…

305
00:16:57,549 --> 00:16:59,017
<i>Just as I led them to first place,</i>

306
00:16:59,018 --> 00:17:01,986
<i>I will absolutely make Super Soman</i>

307
00:17:01,987 --> 00:17:03,287
<i>the top brand.</i>

308
00:17:03,288 --> 00:17:03,989
‎SOMAN CEO
‎HITOSHI ICHIMANDA

309
00:17:04,723 --> 00:17:06,257
<i>Our goal is to build</i>

310
00:17:06,258 --> 00:17:09,494
<i>a new infrastructure for life
that supports people's smiles.</i>

311
00:17:09,495 --> 00:17:13,465
<i>Super Soman will brighten this country,
starting from the dinner table.</i>

312
00:17:14,033 --> 00:17:15,634
If we launched
an acquisition bid against you,

313
00:17:16,201 --> 00:17:17,703
you'd be done in seconds.

314
00:17:19,104 --> 00:17:20,806
Ichimanda…

315
00:17:30,315 --> 00:17:31,783
Is Eito okay?

316
00:17:31,784 --> 00:17:33,752
Well, he hit his head.

317
00:17:36,188 --> 00:17:37,355
True.

318
00:17:37,356 --> 00:17:38,424
I'm going for it!

319
00:17:39,725 --> 00:17:41,860
Once I decide, I never back down.

320
00:17:43,996 --> 00:17:47,933
SUPER SOMAN - ARAKAWA STORE
TWO WEEKS UNTIL GRAND OPENING

321
00:17:48,901 --> 00:17:51,569
Akari Croquette?
Akari Minced Meat Croquette?

322
00:17:51,570 --> 00:17:54,906
I want to make this famous
and revitalize the shopping street.

323
00:17:54,907 --> 00:17:55,840
MUROTA BUTCHER SHOP

324
00:17:55,841 --> 00:17:57,975
We'll do it if it's fine with you.

325
00:17:57,976 --> 00:18:00,511
We want to emphasize local food

326
00:18:00,512 --> 00:18:03,347
and also develop new products,
something that really stands out visually.

327
00:18:03,348 --> 00:18:05,316
Shall we try it if Eito says so?

328
00:18:05,317 --> 00:18:09,488
I want to create a local mascot
for Akari Shopping Street.

329
00:18:10,322 --> 00:18:11,656
A local mascot?!

330
00:18:11,657 --> 00:18:14,492
- But who’s going to design it?
- Right?

331
00:18:14,493 --> 00:18:17,295
- It's gotta be Sarasa.
- Sarasa?

332
00:18:17,296 --> 00:18:19,330
She's a great artist.

333
00:18:19,331 --> 00:18:21,566
She's won tons of awards
since she was little.

334
00:18:21,567 --> 00:18:28,440
IKETANI PRINTING FACTORY

335
00:18:52,364 --> 00:18:55,467
MUROTA BUTCHER SHOP
AKARI SHOPPING STREET SPECIALTY

336
00:18:56,768 --> 00:18:57,769
Wow.

337
00:19:00,439 --> 00:19:01,707
Incredible.

338
00:19:04,143 --> 00:19:05,144
Wonderful.

339
00:19:06,078 --> 00:19:07,379
What's wrong?

340
00:19:08,313 --> 00:19:13,452
No, your art is just so beautiful.

341
00:19:15,621 --> 00:19:17,322
Thank you!

342
00:19:19,391 --> 00:19:22,494
Actually, there's something
I want to ask you.

343
00:19:23,595 --> 00:19:27,966
I want to create a local mascot
for Akari Shopping Street.

344
00:19:28,667 --> 00:19:30,168
A local mascot?

345
00:19:30,169 --> 00:19:32,304
Suddenly? Just like that?

346
00:19:36,708 --> 00:19:38,377
Okay. Done.

347
00:19:41,079 --> 00:19:44,582
Ta-da! I'm calling it "Akari-nu."

348
00:19:44,583 --> 00:19:45,651
What do you think?

349
00:19:48,954 --> 00:19:50,956
You did this in just 30 minutes?

350
00:19:53,192 --> 00:19:54,426
Sarasa, you're a genius.

351
00:19:56,094 --> 00:19:57,729
You're being too generous, Eito.

352
00:19:58,430 --> 00:20:02,433
I want to make this charming character

353
00:20:02,434 --> 00:20:04,769
into a statue to serve

354
00:20:04,770 --> 00:20:07,539
as Akari Shopping Street's landmark.
How should we go about it?

355
00:20:10,175 --> 00:20:12,343
Leave it to us!

356
00:20:12,344 --> 00:20:14,212
We'll make something great!

357
00:20:14,213 --> 00:20:16,081
We'll knock it out by tomorrow.

358
00:20:16,715 --> 00:20:20,052
<i>A couple of idiots
who raise anxiety instead of spirits.</i>

359
00:20:25,757 --> 00:20:27,859
AKARI-NU

360
00:20:51,550 --> 00:20:52,450
Looks good!

361
00:20:52,451 --> 00:20:53,451
So?

362
00:20:53,452 --> 00:20:55,119
- Almost…
- Not yet.

363
00:20:55,120 --> 00:20:57,288
- Okay!
- Good!

364
00:20:57,289 --> 00:20:59,358
Ready, go! Boom!

365
00:21:01,360 --> 00:21:02,394
SHOPPING STREET

366
00:21:05,731 --> 00:21:09,801
AKARI-NU

367
00:21:10,669 --> 00:21:13,772
<i>From that sad excuse for a meeting</i>

368
00:21:14,373 --> 00:21:17,809
<i>to this level of quality
in just half a day…</i>

369
00:21:21,747 --> 00:21:22,848
<i>This is the kind of skill</i>

370
00:21:24,249 --> 00:21:26,618
<i>worthy of</i> Shitamachi Rocket,

371
00:21:27,185 --> 00:21:30,656
<i>the hit drama from two years from now.</i>

372
00:21:32,524 --> 00:21:34,593
- What's wrong, Eito?
- Well…

373
00:21:35,627 --> 00:21:36,928
I'm just moved.

374
00:21:40,232 --> 00:21:42,033
You guys are productive idiots.

375
00:21:42,034 --> 00:21:44,802
- Hey!
- You couldn't give a better compliment?

376
00:21:44,803 --> 00:21:46,837
Well, he seems happy,
so I guess it's fine.

377
00:21:46,838 --> 00:21:47,673
Right?

378
00:21:48,273 --> 00:21:51,075
Wait. In this empty shop,

379
00:21:51,076 --> 00:21:54,712
I want to sell Akari-nu merchandise.
Any ideas?

380
00:21:54,713 --> 00:21:56,947
- Merchandise?
- Merchandise?

381
00:21:56,948 --> 00:21:58,616
- Hey, look!
- You can do it, right?

382
00:21:58,617 --> 00:21:59,850
- Look!
- Huh?

383
00:21:59,851 --> 00:22:04,222
The new menu items, the Shitamachi Burger
and the Shitamachi Rice Burger.

384
00:22:05,090 --> 00:22:06,658
<i>Great visuals.</i>

385
00:22:07,693 --> 00:22:09,895
<i>People will want
to take pictures of these.</i>

386
00:22:10,595 --> 00:22:13,398
<i>Once the Instagram era comes,
these will go viral.</i>

387
00:22:15,233 --> 00:22:16,201
Wonderful.

388
00:22:18,570 --> 00:22:19,470
Yeah!

389
00:22:19,471 --> 00:22:21,672
- Great, huh?
- Yeah.

390
00:22:21,673 --> 00:22:25,609
LOTTERY

391
00:22:25,610 --> 00:22:29,146
We prepared sales and a lottery

392
00:22:29,147 --> 00:22:31,683
to compete with Super Soman,

393
00:22:32,451 --> 00:22:34,886
but without customers, none of it matters.

394
00:22:36,221 --> 00:22:37,222
<i>Damn.</i>

395
00:22:37,823 --> 00:22:40,124
<i>I got so caught up
with those productive idiots</i>

396
00:22:40,125 --> 00:22:42,461
<i>that I neglected PR.</i>

397
00:22:46,865 --> 00:22:49,767
I see. So a high school freshman

398
00:22:49,768 --> 00:22:52,703
looks like an adult
to a third-grade middle school student.

399
00:22:52,704 --> 00:22:55,773
That was the 100-subscriber

400
00:22:55,774 --> 00:22:57,875
Q&A special!

401
00:22:57,876 --> 00:23:01,879
Stay tuned

402
00:23:01,880 --> 00:23:04,082
for more of Megane-kun's daily life!

403
00:23:10,422 --> 00:23:12,456
Still only 100 subscribers, huh?

404
00:23:12,457 --> 00:23:13,891
100 SUBSCRIBERS

405
00:23:13,892 --> 00:23:15,694
Are you Megane-kun?

406
00:23:16,261 --> 00:23:18,129
I have a job offer for you.

407
00:23:18,130 --> 00:23:22,400
A food report on the shopping street.
The pay is 100,000 yen.

408
00:23:22,401 --> 00:23:24,102
That much?

409
00:23:25,003 --> 00:23:27,938
But I don't have many subscribers.

410
00:23:27,939 --> 00:23:30,107
If you change your name
by the end of the year,

411
00:23:30,108 --> 00:23:32,009
I think you'll go viral.

412
00:23:32,010 --> 00:23:33,612
Change my name?

413
00:23:34,179 --> 00:23:37,149
How about "Mega-kun"?

414
00:23:37,716 --> 00:23:41,051
<i>Mega-kun's shopping street feature!</i>

415
00:23:41,052 --> 00:23:44,088
<i>Today, I'm visiting Akari Shopping Street</i>

416
00:23:44,089 --> 00:23:46,290
<i>and meeting Akari-nu! So cute!</i>

417
00:23:46,291 --> 00:23:48,893
<i>So many cute things!</i>

418
00:23:48,894 --> 00:23:50,928
<i>Opening is February 5th.</i>

419
00:23:50,929 --> 00:23:52,396
<i>It's the speciality
of Akari Shopping Street!</i>

420
00:23:52,397 --> 00:23:54,765
<i>The Akari Croquette
and the Akari Minced Meat Croquette.</i>

421
00:23:54,766 --> 00:23:55,699
<i>Let me dig in!</i>

422
00:23:55,700 --> 00:23:57,169
STARTING FOOD REVIEW

423
00:23:57,736 --> 00:24:00,704
This is amazing!
And here's the Shitamachi Burger.

424
00:24:00,705 --> 00:24:03,507
Looks incredible!
It's big for one person, but…

425
00:24:03,508 --> 00:24:05,609
<i>If you come with your friend…</i>

426
00:24:05,610 --> 00:24:07,545
- <i>Enjoy this burger…</i>
- Someone watches this?

427
00:24:07,546 --> 00:24:09,847
He's not famous.

428
00:24:09,848 --> 00:24:12,484
- Can this really be good advertising?
- Yeah.

429
00:24:13,351 --> 00:24:16,254
Eito is working hard. Let him be.

430
00:24:19,124 --> 00:24:19,958
What are you doing?

431
00:24:21,326 --> 00:24:22,227
This…

432
00:24:23,495 --> 00:24:25,496
- Eito asked us to.
- Huh?

433
00:24:25,497 --> 00:24:26,464
What?

434
00:24:26,465 --> 00:24:27,798
See?

435
00:24:27,799 --> 00:24:29,600
- Oh!
- How cute!

436
00:24:29,601 --> 00:24:33,538
SUPER SOMAN - ARAKAWA STORE
OPENS TOMORROW

437
00:24:39,177 --> 00:24:41,713
AKARI SHOPPING STREET

438
00:24:49,287 --> 00:24:50,322
Incredible!

439
00:24:51,823 --> 00:24:53,891
The shopping street
looks so much brighter!

440
00:24:53,892 --> 00:24:56,495
SHOPPING STREET

441
00:24:57,629 --> 00:24:58,964
But why didn't you pursue

442
00:24:59,664 --> 00:25:02,100
a career using this talent?

443
00:25:03,001 --> 00:25:04,202
What's the matter, Eito?

444
00:25:05,770 --> 00:25:07,538
You already know
I dropped out of art school

445
00:25:07,539 --> 00:25:10,275
when Dad got hospitalized, right?

446
00:25:12,444 --> 00:25:13,345
Of course.

447
00:25:14,145 --> 00:25:18,116
But seeing this now…

448
00:25:19,784 --> 00:25:21,620
Stop it. It's too late.

449
00:25:22,821 --> 00:25:25,690
I gave up on that a long time ago.

450
00:25:29,294 --> 00:25:33,365
Anyway, let's hurry. Tomorrow is
Super Soman's grand opening, right?

451
00:25:34,099 --> 00:25:34,966
Right.

452
00:25:35,934 --> 00:25:37,635
SUPER SOMAN GRAND OPENING
ARAKAWA STORE

453
00:25:37,636 --> 00:25:41,605
The line at Super Soman is so long.
Everyone’s pushing.

454
00:25:41,606 --> 00:25:44,008
Compared to that,

455
00:25:44,009 --> 00:25:44,975
not a single customer…

456
00:25:44,976 --> 00:25:45,910
WELCOME TO AKARI SHOPPING STREET

457
00:25:45,911 --> 00:25:47,445
…has come to our shopping street.

458
00:25:48,013 --> 00:25:51,782
Well, the effort we all put in
will at least be a good memory.

459
00:25:51,783 --> 00:25:54,152
What memory? Jeez…

460
00:25:59,524 --> 00:26:01,926
AKARI SHOPPING STREET
RAFFLE

461
00:26:01,927 --> 00:26:03,460
That’s looking good.

462
00:26:03,461 --> 00:26:04,563
Yeah.

463
00:26:06,731 --> 00:26:07,566
Okay.

464
00:26:08,199 --> 00:26:09,634
- Over there…
- Oh!

465
00:26:10,201 --> 00:26:12,571
Hey, that’s enough, Eito.

466
00:26:13,238 --> 00:26:16,074
In the end,
we can't beat a big corporation.

467
00:26:16,741 --> 00:26:19,677
Sarasa, with all this nonsense…

468
00:26:19,678 --> 00:26:21,312
Go home and get back to work.

469
00:26:21,313 --> 00:26:22,780
Kinpei, it's a bit early

470
00:26:22,781 --> 00:26:25,683
to be waving the white flag, isn't it?

471
00:26:25,684 --> 00:26:27,953
We haven't lost yet.

472
00:26:28,987 --> 00:26:32,323
Think about it a little more
before you give up.

473
00:26:32,324 --> 00:26:35,326
Saying that is basically admitting
you have no brain.

474
00:26:35,327 --> 00:26:38,362
- Huh?
- Are you living in a fantasy world?

475
00:26:38,363 --> 00:26:40,165
Do you not have a brain?

476
00:26:41,666 --> 00:26:42,634
What's wrong, Eito?

477
00:26:45,337 --> 00:26:47,405
Um…

478
00:26:48,540 --> 00:26:51,643
Giving up without trying
is absolute garbage!

479
00:26:53,211 --> 00:26:54,378
True…

480
00:26:54,379 --> 00:26:56,847
You must have hit your head
in a really bad spot.

481
00:26:56,848 --> 00:27:00,317
Go get checked at the hospital again.
Let's go, everyone!

482
00:27:00,318 --> 00:27:02,020
- Kinpei…
- Come on, Chairman!

483
00:27:03,254 --> 00:27:04,154
Come on, Chairman!

484
00:27:04,155 --> 00:27:06,523
- There it is!
- Found it!

485
00:27:06,524 --> 00:27:07,758
So cute!

486
00:27:07,759 --> 00:27:09,493
She's a charmer, all right.

487
00:27:09,494 --> 00:27:11,462
Can we eat an Akari Croquette?

488
00:27:11,463 --> 00:27:12,363
Yes!

489
00:27:12,364 --> 00:27:14,932
- You can!
- I want to eat…

490
00:27:14,933 --> 00:27:16,200
- Hey!
- Croquette…

491
00:27:16,201 --> 00:27:17,501
- Croquette…
- Welcome!

492
00:27:17,502 --> 00:27:18,969
- Wow!
- Welcome!

493
00:27:18,970 --> 00:27:20,371
- Wow!
- Wait!

494
00:27:20,372 --> 00:27:21,405
- Wait!
- What's going on?

495
00:27:21,406 --> 00:27:22,973
- Hey!
- This is crazy!

496
00:27:22,974 --> 00:27:24,074
Look at them come!

497
00:27:24,075 --> 00:27:26,710
- They're coming!
- Really?

498
00:27:26,711 --> 00:27:28,679
- Amazing!
- I'll upload it to my blog.

499
00:27:28,680 --> 00:27:31,382
Not bad, huh?

500
00:27:31,383 --> 00:27:34,418
Is this because Eito went a little crazy?

501
00:27:34,419 --> 00:27:37,022
Good thing you hit your head, Eito!

502
00:27:37,856 --> 00:27:39,624
It's all thanks to you guys.

503
00:27:40,325 --> 00:27:41,525
- Hey!
- Hey!

504
00:27:41,526 --> 00:27:43,894
- Hey, give me a hand!
- Okay!

505
00:27:43,895 --> 00:27:45,162
Yeah…

506
00:27:45,163 --> 00:27:46,031
You know…

507
00:27:47,232 --> 00:27:48,633
you really are amazing.

508
00:27:51,336 --> 00:27:55,507
Today might actually be a good day.

509
00:27:58,843 --> 00:28:01,780
SIX MONTHS LATER

510
00:28:07,886 --> 00:28:10,988
<i>Here we go!</i> Quiz Deck-Q!

511
00:28:10,989 --> 00:28:13,157
<i>Today's guest is the rising NowTuber</i>

512
00:28:13,158 --> 00:28:15,359
- <i>Mega-kun!</i>
- <i>Hello!</i>

513
00:28:15,360 --> 00:28:19,397
- <i>This is Mega-kun!</i>
- I can't believe how popular he got.

514
00:28:20,398 --> 00:28:23,868
- Looks like Eito had an eye for talent.
- <i>Yes. You know…</i>

515
00:28:24,436 --> 00:28:26,570
WELCOME TO AKARI SHOPPING STREET

516
00:28:26,571 --> 00:28:28,539
FRUIT AND VEGETABLE STORE

517
00:28:28,540 --> 00:28:30,407
Ten fresh croquettes.

518
00:28:30,408 --> 00:28:32,042
Thank you!

519
00:28:32,043 --> 00:28:32,943
- Yes!
- Thank you!

520
00:28:32,944 --> 00:28:33,844
Good luck!

521
00:28:33,845 --> 00:28:36,580
Hideko's shop is really thriving.

522
00:28:36,581 --> 00:28:38,982
- I feel like I'm dreaming!
- Thank you!

523
00:28:38,983 --> 00:28:40,150
Here is fine.

524
00:28:40,151 --> 00:28:41,386
<i>This is still nothing.</i>

525
00:28:42,187 --> 00:28:44,788
<i>I still wouldn't call it success.</i>

526
00:28:44,789 --> 00:28:48,325
- I always knew you would come through.
- Yeah.

527
00:28:48,326 --> 00:28:50,094
Eito, thank you.

528
00:28:50,095 --> 00:28:51,295
Thank you.

529
00:28:51,296 --> 00:28:53,130
- Hey, let's go.
- Yeah.

530
00:28:53,131 --> 00:28:54,431
Let's go help Hideko.

531
00:28:54,432 --> 00:28:56,735
He's in a good mood.

532
00:28:57,736 --> 00:28:58,837
Thanks, Eito.

533
00:28:59,471 --> 00:29:00,505
No.

534
00:29:01,206 --> 00:29:03,640
<i>For now, if this popularity keeps up,</i>

535
00:29:03,641 --> 00:29:05,876
<i>the shopping street will thrive,</i>

536
00:29:05,877 --> 00:29:07,812
<i>the tabs will disappear,</i>

537
00:29:08,747 --> 00:29:11,516
<i>and I'll have built a foundation
for living as Eito Nomoto.</i>

538
00:29:12,050 --> 00:29:14,052
<i>And I'll be able to drink wine.</i>

539
00:29:17,722 --> 00:29:19,224
Oh, about that thing

540
00:29:20,291 --> 00:29:22,026
I mentioned before…

541
00:29:24,729 --> 00:29:25,663
That thing?

542
00:29:29,834 --> 00:29:32,436
Are you going to pretend
it never happened?

543
00:29:32,437 --> 00:29:34,005
Even though you went that far…

544
00:29:35,940 --> 00:29:37,075
That far…

545
00:29:40,678 --> 00:29:41,846
What thing exactly?

546
00:29:42,413 --> 00:29:43,381
Huh?

547
00:29:44,249 --> 00:29:45,150
No…

548
00:29:47,318 --> 00:29:50,688
I forgot. Can you tell me again?

549
00:30:01,099 --> 00:30:03,401
<i>Even as Eito, I still get smacked.</i>

550
00:30:04,602 --> 00:30:05,837
<i>But why?</i>

551
00:30:11,409 --> 00:30:13,211
I have no idea.

552
00:30:16,047 --> 00:30:17,282
What thing?

553
00:30:19,117 --> 00:30:20,385
What is it?

554
00:30:21,820 --> 00:30:23,087
I'm home.

555
00:30:25,523 --> 00:30:26,990
"I'm home"?

556
00:30:26,991 --> 00:30:27,959
<i>Who's there?</i>

557
00:30:29,360 --> 00:30:30,894
Hey! Welcome back!

558
00:30:30,895 --> 00:30:33,096
Eri! How was studying abroad in Australia?

559
00:30:33,097 --> 00:30:36,166
Australia was great!
I made friends with local students,

560
00:30:36,167 --> 00:30:38,602
- and the homestay was wonderful.
- Oh.

561
00:30:38,603 --> 00:30:40,270
Glad you're doing well.

562
00:30:40,271 --> 00:30:42,906
Thanks to Eito,
the shopping street is lively again.

563
00:30:42,907 --> 00:30:45,176
- Is he okay too?
- Look.

564
00:30:46,644 --> 00:30:48,146
Brother!

565
00:30:49,581 --> 00:30:50,748
You look good.

566
00:30:51,950 --> 00:30:53,985
- Well…
- That's good.

567
00:30:54,552 --> 00:30:56,187
<i>Eito's little sister is…</i>

568
00:30:57,055 --> 00:30:59,123
<i>Eri Nomoto, my secretary</i>

569
00:30:59,691 --> 00:31:02,392
<i>from back when I was Kosei Neo.</i>

570
00:31:02,393 --> 00:31:05,762
- Eri! I made curry. Go rest.
- Oh!

571
00:31:05,763 --> 00:31:09,801
Really! I'm happy!

572
00:31:12,937 --> 00:31:14,172
Eri…

573
00:31:15,506 --> 00:31:17,475
What year are you in?

574
00:31:18,509 --> 00:31:20,378
I'm in my fourth year.

575
00:31:21,446 --> 00:31:23,014
I'll need to start job hunting soon.

576
00:31:24,015 --> 00:31:27,585
- <i>Are you going to apply to NEOXIS?</i>
- Souvenir…

577
00:31:28,653 --> 00:31:30,822
Ta-da! Chocolates!

578
00:31:31,456 --> 00:31:32,290
<i>No…</i>

579
00:31:32,924 --> 00:31:36,793
<i>NEOXIS will probably collapse in 2026</i>

580
00:31:36,794 --> 00:31:39,596
<i>when I, the president,</i>

581
00:31:39,597 --> 00:31:42,266
<i>fall to my death.</i>

582
00:31:42,267 --> 00:31:44,601
- <i>Actually…</i>
- Today is also my last day.

583
00:31:44,602 --> 00:31:48,071
- <i>…Eri will quit in disgust before that.</i>
- This is a koala.

584
00:31:48,072 --> 00:31:51,442
<i>Anyway, she can't work there.</i>

585
00:31:52,243 --> 00:31:53,344
<i>I've got to talk her out of it.</i>

586
00:31:56,648 --> 00:31:59,851
My friend who I studied abroad with
invited me to volunteer.

587
00:32:00,551 --> 00:32:02,386
<i>This isn't good.</i>

588
00:32:02,387 --> 00:32:04,321
<i>She'll be drawn to welfare work
and go to NEOXIS.</i>

589
00:32:04,322 --> 00:32:07,090
What kind of field do you prefer?

590
00:32:07,091 --> 00:32:09,027
- Maybe a travel company?
- Oh!

591
00:32:09,594 --> 00:32:11,128
<i>Right.</i>

592
00:32:11,129 --> 00:32:14,198
<i>If so, I should encourage that… Wait, no.</i>

593
00:32:15,099 --> 00:32:18,535
<i>Many travel companies
struggled financially because of COVID.</i>

594
00:32:18,536 --> 00:32:19,703
- Nice.
- Nice.

595
00:32:19,704 --> 00:32:21,239
Any other interests?

596
00:32:22,840 --> 00:32:24,875
I'm interested in the gaming industry.

597
00:32:24,876 --> 00:32:28,413
That's the one. Demand will go
through the roof during COVID.

598
00:32:30,014 --> 00:32:32,249
Brother, you're acting weird.

599
00:32:32,250 --> 00:32:33,850
As your brother,

600
00:32:33,851 --> 00:32:36,521
I strongly recommend the gaming industry.

601
00:32:40,758 --> 00:32:43,361
Dad! He's definitely not right!

602
00:32:46,130 --> 00:32:48,231
From the NEOXIS president
who's currently on a business trip.

603
00:32:48,232 --> 00:32:51,468
A gift to celebrate
the firm's 15th anniversary.

604
00:32:51,469 --> 00:32:52,636
Huh?

605
00:32:52,637 --> 00:32:55,139
Going out of your way to look after
a startup like NEOXIS…

606
00:32:55,707 --> 00:32:58,742
Togo, isn't that a bit much?

607
00:32:58,743 --> 00:33:00,645
Please, be gentle with me.

608
00:33:01,312 --> 00:33:03,881
Super Soman is doing well, isn't it?

609
00:33:04,782 --> 00:33:09,153
Yes, but the Arakawa location
is lagging behind.

610
00:33:10,154 --> 00:33:11,556
You seem displeased.

611
00:33:12,724 --> 00:33:16,060
We didn't expect a local shopping street
to be stealing our customers.

612
00:33:16,794 --> 00:33:17,862
How so?

613
00:33:18,596 --> 00:33:21,933
Young people are making a buzz about it
on social media.

614
00:33:24,535 --> 00:33:27,138
It might be a new trend.

615
00:33:27,972 --> 00:33:29,207
Oh!

616
00:33:32,310 --> 00:33:33,477
‎NOMOTO DRY CLEANERS

617
00:33:33,478 --> 00:33:35,779
The game company Eri is aiming for…

618
00:33:35,780 --> 00:33:37,981
…Wao Game, is famous for <i>Punipuni Attack</i>.

619
00:33:37,982 --> 00:33:41,518
- It's a maker destined to go global.
<i>- Venture capital firm…</i>

620
00:33:41,519 --> 00:33:43,187
Eito endorses it.

621
00:33:43,955 --> 00:33:45,989
- I hope I get in.
- <i>Next up…</i>

622
00:33:45,990 --> 00:33:48,359
- Yeah…
- <i>Today's venture company…</i>

623
00:33:49,894 --> 00:33:51,829
<i>Let me introduce NEOXIS.</i>

624
00:33:52,597 --> 00:33:56,366
<i>In under two years, they've made
their business software a massive hit.</i>

625
00:33:56,367 --> 00:33:59,136
<i>Here is Tatsuki Tomono of NEOXIS,</i>

626
00:33:59,137 --> 00:34:01,338
<i>a rising star in the IT industry.</i>

627
00:34:01,339 --> 00:34:02,305
NEOXIS
FOR THE PEOPLE

628
00:34:02,306 --> 00:34:04,809
- <i>Nice to meet you.</i>
- <i>Nice to meet you.</i>

629
00:34:05,843 --> 00:34:08,478
<i>Our company operates under the mission</i>

630
00:34:08,479 --> 00:34:10,981
<i>of "For the People,"
championed by President Neo.</i>

631
00:34:10,982 --> 00:34:14,217
<i>We've been working
to be of service to people.</i>

632
00:34:14,218 --> 00:34:16,420
- That's cool!
- <i>I heard</i>

633
00:34:16,421 --> 00:34:18,989
- <i>you started with welfare services.</i>
- Huh?

634
00:34:18,990 --> 00:34:23,361
<i>Yes, NEOXIS aims for a world
where people help one another.</i>

635
00:34:25,696 --> 00:34:28,632
So they started with programs
to support others.

636
00:34:28,633 --> 00:34:30,368
- <i>What luck!</i>
- <i>I think you noticed…</i>

637
00:34:31,169 --> 00:34:33,504
<i>I have to get Eri
into Wao Game no matter what.</i>

638
00:34:37,809 --> 00:34:38,943
We're eating right now.

639
00:34:39,544 --> 00:34:45,149
Once we're done,
let's practice for your interview.

640
00:34:47,285 --> 00:34:48,419
- Okay.
- Okay.

641
00:34:49,120 --> 00:34:53,491
NOMOTO DRY CLEANERS
ONE WEEK LATER

642
00:34:54,092 --> 00:34:56,326
I'll do my best in the interview!

643
00:34:56,327 --> 00:34:59,362
If you follow what we practiced,
you'll be fine.

644
00:34:59,363 --> 00:35:00,564
- Yeah.
- Okay.

645
00:35:00,565 --> 00:35:01,498
Good luck!

646
00:35:01,499 --> 00:35:03,100
I'm off!

647
00:35:03,101 --> 00:35:03,935
Take care.

648
00:35:09,107 --> 00:35:13,211
INTERVIEW FOR WAO GAME

649
00:35:15,179 --> 00:35:17,380
Hey, Brother.

650
00:35:17,381 --> 00:35:18,583
<i>How was it?</i>

651
00:35:20,151 --> 00:35:22,986
I think I failed the interview.

652
00:35:22,987 --> 00:35:23,987
<i>Huh?</i>

653
00:35:23,988 --> 00:35:25,957
I'm sorry for all your help.

654
00:35:27,158 --> 00:35:29,894
<i>But I'll look somewhere else.</i>

655
00:35:30,461 --> 00:35:32,362
No, try somewhere else…

656
00:35:32,363 --> 00:35:34,398
Hold on.

657
00:35:35,066 --> 00:35:39,002
There are other gaming companies.
Find what went wrong,

658
00:35:39,003 --> 00:35:43,840
learn from it, and move on. Then… Hello?

659
00:35:43,841 --> 00:35:45,243
Hello?

660
00:35:52,750 --> 00:35:53,584
Hello?

661
00:36:00,625 --> 00:36:01,725
- Hey!
- Oh!

662
00:36:01,726 --> 00:36:03,661
Watch out! Be careful!

663
00:36:05,196 --> 00:36:06,264
Are you okay?

664
00:36:09,133 --> 00:36:11,101
EXAMINATION ROOM

665
00:36:11,102 --> 00:36:14,070
- Please take care.
- Thank you.

666
00:36:14,071 --> 00:36:15,605
- Are you all right?
- Yeah.

667
00:36:15,606 --> 00:36:17,708
I'm fine now.

668
00:36:18,476 --> 00:36:20,577
You really saved me.

669
00:36:20,578 --> 00:36:23,447
Helping someone in need is only natural.

670
00:36:24,749 --> 00:36:27,618
Um… You're from NEOXIS, aren't you?

671
00:36:28,252 --> 00:36:29,786
I saw you on TV…

672
00:36:29,787 --> 00:36:32,623
- You saw me on TV?
- "For the People."

673
00:36:34,158 --> 00:36:36,393
That's President Neo's mission.

674
00:36:36,394 --> 00:36:39,129
He's someone with both vision and drive,

675
00:36:39,130 --> 00:36:40,898
truly someone you can rely on.

676
00:36:48,105 --> 00:36:49,006
She's late.

677
00:36:50,374 --> 00:36:53,177
She's not a little kid.
She'll come back eventually.

678
00:36:56,847 --> 00:36:59,250
- I'm home.
- Welcome back.

679
00:36:59,917 --> 00:37:03,887
Welcome back. You're late.
We were worried.

680
00:37:03,888 --> 00:37:06,356
Sorry, I fell and hurt myself.

681
00:37:06,357 --> 00:37:07,257
Huh?

682
00:37:07,258 --> 00:37:09,927
Someone helped me and walked me home.

683
00:37:11,862 --> 00:37:13,898
- Come in.
- Excuse me.

684
00:37:14,465 --> 00:37:16,767
Nice to meet you. I'm Tomono.

685
00:37:20,171 --> 00:37:23,274
Thank you… so much.

686
00:37:24,642 --> 00:37:27,645
Didn't you come to our office
the other day?

687
00:37:29,013 --> 00:37:32,650
I thought you looked
just like our president.

688
00:37:34,185 --> 00:37:35,119
No…

689
00:37:35,720 --> 00:37:36,653
No…

690
00:37:36,654 --> 00:37:38,255
I have a common face.

691
00:37:38,256 --> 00:37:40,223
No! I mean…

692
00:37:40,224 --> 00:37:43,027
You really look just like him!

693
00:37:43,961 --> 00:37:46,631
Though the president
is a bit more intimidating.

694
00:37:49,300 --> 00:37:51,936
Anyway, Brother, I've decided

695
00:37:52,670 --> 00:37:54,372
to join NEOXIS.

696
00:37:56,173 --> 00:37:57,741
What?

697
00:37:57,742 --> 00:38:00,110
On the very day I gave up on Wao Game,

698
00:38:00,111 --> 00:38:02,946
meeting Mr. Tomono
from NEOXIS feels like fate.

699
00:38:02,947 --> 00:38:05,916
He even said he'd be happy to have me.

700
00:38:08,119 --> 00:38:10,288
<i>How did this happen so fast?</i>

701
00:38:11,322 --> 00:38:12,890
<i>I have to stand my ground.</i>

702
00:38:13,924 --> 00:38:15,660
Tomono. I mean, Mr. Tomono.

703
00:38:16,227 --> 00:38:19,697
- Yes?
- What did you say to my sister?

704
00:38:20,865 --> 00:38:23,166
- Huh?
- "For the People."

705
00:38:23,167 --> 00:38:26,536
Your president's mission

706
00:38:26,537 --> 00:38:30,006
is certainly admirable.
But I sense hypocrisy.

707
00:38:30,007 --> 00:38:31,441
Hey, Brother!

708
00:38:31,442 --> 00:38:35,278
The welfare work is just a means
to get the company's name out there.

709
00:38:35,279 --> 00:38:38,815
Isn't NEOXIS really
a devil in the skin of a humanitarian?

710
00:38:38,816 --> 00:38:40,450
Don't you think so?

711
00:38:40,451 --> 00:38:41,985
How can you say that right now?

712
00:38:41,986 --> 00:38:44,387
It pains me more than anyone
to speak badly of Kosei Neo!

713
00:38:44,388 --> 00:38:46,290
- I'm so sorry.
- But I have to say it.

714
00:38:47,858 --> 00:38:49,126
How many more years is it?

715
00:38:49,627 --> 00:38:51,328
Seven years. In seven years,

716
00:38:51,329 --> 00:38:53,396
a pandemic will throw
the world into chaos.

717
00:38:53,397 --> 00:38:55,565
Then Tomono… I mean, Mr. Tomono,

718
00:38:55,566 --> 00:38:57,634
will see me… No, I mean, Kosei Neo,

719
00:38:57,635 --> 00:38:59,235
in a completely different light.

720
00:38:59,236 --> 00:39:00,870
The world thrown into chaos?

721
00:39:00,871 --> 00:39:02,739
Stop saying things that don't make sense!

722
00:39:02,740 --> 00:39:03,973
- Eito.
- Huh?

723
00:39:03,974 --> 00:39:07,043
Enough. I understand
you're worried about your sister,

724
00:39:07,044 --> 00:39:08,745
but Eri made her choice. Leave her alone.

725
00:39:08,746 --> 00:39:11,248
Dad, we need to stand firm.

726
00:39:12,183 --> 00:39:14,317
Anyway, please leave for today.

727
00:39:14,318 --> 00:39:15,286
- Hey!
- Oh!

728
00:39:16,420 --> 00:39:18,689
Stop being so rude!

729
00:39:22,593 --> 00:39:23,494
You okay?

730
00:39:25,096 --> 00:39:26,296
<i>Apparently,</i>

731
00:39:26,297 --> 00:39:28,999
<i>the women in this town move fast.</i>

732
00:39:34,839 --> 00:39:37,241
I'm here for my job interview.
I'm Eri Nomoto.

733
00:39:39,944 --> 00:39:43,647
<i>Is it just like in the sci-fi novels?</i>

734
00:39:44,248 --> 00:39:46,950
<i>Can a person's fate really not be changed?</i>

735
00:39:46,951 --> 00:39:48,586
<i>Are you not allowed to change it?</i>

736
00:39:50,855 --> 00:39:51,789
Oh…

737
00:39:52,590 --> 00:39:53,824
Eri's brother.

738
00:39:58,662 --> 00:40:01,098
You're really worried
about your sister, aren't you?

739
00:40:01,866 --> 00:40:03,601
No, I just happened to be nearby.

740
00:40:05,035 --> 00:40:06,570
Tomono.

741
00:40:09,039 --> 00:40:10,174
<i>Togo.</i>

742
00:40:10,741 --> 00:40:11,875
Sorry.

743
00:40:11,876 --> 00:40:13,710
Let me introduce you.

744
00:40:13,711 --> 00:40:14,779
- This is CEO…
- <i>That's right.</i>

745
00:40:16,080 --> 00:40:19,717
- Nice to meet you.
- <i>Back then, Togo had introduced me</i>

746
00:40:20,284 --> 00:40:24,054
- <i>to Tsuchiya and Takarabe.</i>
- Nice to meet you.

747
00:40:26,757 --> 00:40:27,625
<i>Wait a moment.</i>

748
00:40:29,026 --> 00:40:30,127
<i>Could one of them…</i>

749
00:40:31,929 --> 00:40:33,330
<i>be the one…</i>

750
00:40:35,299 --> 00:40:38,002
<i>who pushed me?</i>

751
00:40:39,937 --> 00:40:41,572
<i>At some point,</i>

752
00:40:42,072 --> 00:40:44,675
<i>each of them will develop
a grudge against me.</i>

753
00:40:45,376 --> 00:40:48,212
SANYOKAN BUILDING

754
00:40:49,180 --> 00:40:51,282
<i>To uncover who,</i>

755
00:40:52,149 --> 00:40:54,118
<i>could I use Eri</i>

756
00:40:54,685 --> 00:40:57,588
<i>to keep an eye on them from the inside?</i>

757
00:40:58,389 --> 00:40:59,423
<i>Is that even okay to do?</i>

758
00:41:03,894 --> 00:41:06,030
You really do look like Neo.

759
00:41:10,301 --> 00:41:12,336
Tomono told me

760
00:41:13,337 --> 00:41:14,672
that you called Neo

761
00:41:15,573 --> 00:41:19,410
a devil in the skin of a humanitarian.

762
00:41:20,478 --> 00:41:23,814
<i>That's the exact phrase
you used with me once.</i>

763
00:41:24,715 --> 00:41:26,450
I share the same view.

764
00:41:27,218 --> 00:41:30,186
- <i>I see.</i>
- You also said a pandemic

765
00:41:30,187 --> 00:41:33,123
would throw the world into chaos.

766
00:41:36,360 --> 00:41:38,395
Is there any basis for that claim?

767
00:41:40,264 --> 00:41:42,132
I suppose it was…

768
00:41:43,234 --> 00:41:45,669
more of an impulse.

769
00:41:46,670 --> 00:41:47,705
But you also predicted

770
00:41:48,839 --> 00:41:53,511
that Mega-kun
would break through as a popular NowTuber.

771
00:41:54,078 --> 00:41:56,380
He's a creator I like.

772
00:41:57,681 --> 00:41:59,349
And the idea that

773
00:41:59,350 --> 00:42:01,651
<i>photogenic food spread
through influencers and blogs</i>

774
00:42:01,652 --> 00:42:06,357
would make for good advertising…
Was that also you?

775
00:42:06,957 --> 00:42:10,361
I was grasping at anything I could.

776
00:42:11,795 --> 00:42:15,866
Perhaps you have a gift
to analyze the present

777
00:42:17,234 --> 00:42:20,804
and predict the future.

778
00:42:24,308 --> 00:42:25,242
Could you give me

779
00:42:26,544 --> 00:42:28,612
one piece of advice?

780
00:42:29,313 --> 00:42:31,447
A client has asked me

781
00:42:31,448 --> 00:42:34,818
to feature a figure skater
in an advertisement.

782
00:42:36,020 --> 00:42:40,491
If only I knew who would win at
the Sochi Olympics, it'd save me trouble.

783
00:42:41,225 --> 00:42:43,093
Who should I bet on?

784
00:42:45,195 --> 00:42:46,430
What would you do?

785
00:42:47,698 --> 00:42:49,934
I won't ask you for free, of course.

786
00:42:51,702 --> 00:42:52,736
Ten million yen.

787
00:42:55,839 --> 00:42:58,575
<i>Exactly 10 million yen in debt.</i>

788
00:42:58,576 --> 00:42:59,643
LOAN NOTE

789
00:43:03,714 --> 00:43:04,848
I would go with…

790
00:43:06,717 --> 00:43:09,687
Yuzuru Hanyu.

791
00:43:16,226 --> 00:43:18,394
FIRST IN JAPAN

792
00:43:18,395 --> 00:43:21,799
YUZURU HANYU
GOLD MEDAL

793
00:43:36,280 --> 00:43:38,482
Here's the 10 million we agreed on.

794
00:43:39,717 --> 00:43:42,152
May I really accept this?

795
00:43:45,155 --> 00:43:48,292
I have a feeling we'll have
a long partnership ahead of us.

796
00:43:52,062 --> 00:43:54,431
<i>For some reason, meeting Togo in this body</i>

797
00:43:55,299 --> 00:43:58,135
<i>has made something clearer.</i>

798
00:43:59,937 --> 00:44:02,005
<i>I truly am living</i>

799
00:44:02,006 --> 00:44:05,209
<i>inside Eito Nomoto's body.</i>

800
00:44:08,045 --> 00:44:10,948
<i>But whoever killed the real me,</i>

801
00:44:11,649 --> 00:44:14,818
<i>Kosei Neo…</i>

802
00:44:15,452 --> 00:44:16,920
<i>I will find them.</i>

803
00:44:18,922 --> 00:44:19,555
‎NEXT EPISODE
‎THE SHOPPING STREET BECAME INCORPORATED?

804
00:44:19,556 --> 00:44:22,859
‎Let's set up a company.
‎Akari Shopping Street Co., Ltd.

805
00:44:22,860 --> 00:44:24,961
‎Your brother may be a genius!

806
00:44:24,962 --> 00:44:27,864
‎-"Where did I propose?"
‎-Propose?

807
00:44:27,865 --> 00:44:29,966
<i>‎It moved my heart.</i>

808
00:44:29,967 --> 00:44:33,302
‎Maybe it’s what I want to do
‎with the time I have left.

809
00:44:33,303 --> 00:44:33,936
‎THIS DRAMA IS FICTION

810
00:44:33,937 --> 00:44:34,872
Subtitle translation by: Ken Nishizaki
